node.text:
Today I can finally share a passion project I’ve been working on together with @66north and @oceanmissionsiceland ⛵️

Combining science, education, and adventure, Ocean Missions is a non-profit organisation based out of Húsavík, Iceland, dedicated to research and raise awareness of the issues we’re facing with our Oceans. Operating on a 70-year-old wooden sailboat, the team gathers valuable information for both scientists and policy makers and seeks to spread awareness about marine life, plastic polution and the Ocean’s health, with the aim of encouraging others to take action.

I feel lucky and proud to be a part of this amazing group of people that want to learn from each other, inspire and take action when it comes to these issues.  This wouldn’t be possible without the passion-driven people behind the project; Belen, Daniel, Heimir and Charla that have all dedicated their lives to the oceans. 

While sailing around the coast of Iceland we witness the severity of the plastic pollution, which ranges from tiny micro-plastics in the ocean to large, abandoned fishing equipment on our beaches. It's everywhere. The scale of the problem is even larger than I would have imagined.  
The oceans concerns all of us. It’s important to Iceland with whales returning every summer to their main feeding ground. We are just a tiny part of nature. We belong to it, and we need to protect it – not exploit it.   Filmed by the talented: @catkoppel 

#66North #GlacierFriday #OceanMissions @northsailing

node.text:
The drone we’ve all been waiting for is out: DJI Mavic 3 

I’ve been travelling around the Alps, Dolomites and Iceland lately with this power drone in my backpack, and I can honestly say I’m impressed. Incredible image quality, two lenses, 4k 120fps filming and 46 minutes of flight time. 

The longer flight time has allowed me to reach places I otherwise couldn’t with drones. This one will change the game for what’s possible to capture with drones. 

It has been so fun to be part of this launch and flying the Mavic 3. Well done @djiglobal on building the best drone I’ve ever flown. It will join me on all my adventures from now on. 

 #DJIMavic3 #ImagingAboveEverything

with @xiaomi.global ⛵️ I love sailing and the freedom it gives, so I set sails for a day in Croatia and brought the Xiaomi 11T Pro to capture it. 

The camera in this phone is really amazing and I’m so happy with the outcome of this film. 

It captures the vibe of waking up next to the ocean and spending a day with wind in the sails. 

Shooting in 4k 60fps, the Xiaomi is the perfect tool for shooting on the go and capturing great memories.
#Xiaomi11TPro  #cinemagic #ad

Yayy, it’s out! Here’s my recommendations for spending an adventure filled day on this volcanic island with @icelandair ✈️

Only a short flight from Reykjavík, you’ll find Vestmannaeyjar islands. Famous for volcanoes, puffins, ocean adventures and festivals. 

Here’s my list for recommendations:
- Go ATVing with @volcanoatv 
- Do the @ribsafari 
- Hike Heimaklettur
- Grab dinner

Would you like to see more of these Vlog style videos? 😁

#Icelandair

node.text:
Earlier this summer I traveled to East of Iceland with @icelandair ✈️ This part of Iceland is full of wonders, deep canyons, hot springs and wildlife. 

All those incredible places, are close to the largest town of the East, Egilsstaðir, where @icelandair flies to. 

Here are some of the activities we did, so save this post for your travels to East Iceland. 👇🏼
- Hike up Hengifoss
- Hike Stuðlagil Canyon
- Had organic lunch at @modir_jord 
- The 8km waterfall hike at Laugarfell
- Visit the hot spring at Laugarfell afterwards
- Have coffee in the cute town of Seydisfjordur
- Relax at spa @vokbaths 
- Have incredible sushi at @nordaustur_sushi_bar 
- Explore the fjords 

Have you been to East Iceland? Or would you like to visit those places? 

#Iceland

Nothing compares to a good cup of coffee in nature, getting disconnected from the busy life, but reconnected to the present moment. ☕️🙏 These days I’m only “allowed” one cup a day, so I’m very focused these days on that it has to be perfect 😆🤌🏼

Our latest TV-project for @bki_island ☕️ That recently swapped over to more eco-friendly packages for their 100% arabica coffee. 

Shot by 🎥: @davidgodi

node.text:
Guys this is an exciting opportunity. Hotel Rangá is looking for a photographer to live with them for one month. Those of you that have followed me for awhile, know that this is one of my favourite hotels in Iceland. 

The job title is “It’s first official Northern Light Catcher”. As the job will include catching the beautiful lights in the environment of the hotel. As well as exploring all the magic of Iceland.

Please do me a favour and tag your photographer friends or favourite photographer to let them know about this opportunity 😄

Flights will be covered ✈️

Check out the link in stories to find out more information and apply! 😄

Good luck to you 🤞🏼@hotelranga

node.text:
Music video premiere, to the latest song by @musicbyragnar 🎵 : I’m at home. 

The best thing about travelling, is to get a bit of distance from the nature in Iceland. Because each time we come back, it feels like experiencing it for the first time all over again. 

The video portrays the journey from the airport back to Ragnars home farm in Hali, the cute yellow house that I have good memories from. The drive there is incredible, where you’ll pass waterfalls, glaciers and black sand beaches. I’m Ragnars mind, that drive always gives him the feeling that he’s finally home, so we wanted to capture that. 

I hope you enjoy and make sure to check out Ragnars music on Spotify and on his profile, for some more Icelandic music. 

😍❤️

node.text:
I went on a super fun day-trip the other day. It’s a perfect itinerary from Reykjavík capital and in this video I share it with you.

Let me know in comments how you liked the video 😊

This area is often overlooked by travellers, but we can say that The Volcano has truly put it on the map in mix with the famous Blue Lagoon. 

Here’s my itinerary: 

Reykjavík - Krýsuvík - Kleifarvatn - Seltún - The Volcano - The Blue Lagoon - Reykjavík. 

Icelandair has great offers these days, for Iceland, volcano thirsty travellers 😄🌋 ✈️

#Iceland

node.text:
Sailing around the fjords of Iceland, scouting lines everyday and living on a yacht. We had a incredible days where we hiked and skied everyday, with nature as our bedroom, far away from civilisation. Together with the Aurora Arktika family. 

During that week we had seals swimming curiously around our boat, had untracked powder and did too many ocean swims to remember. 🌊

This week also makes you truly appreciate nature, disconnecting from the outside world and drop the phone and wifi.

Our bodies got so sore from all the hiking and skiing but it feels so good.

So who’s joining next trip?? 💁🏼‍♀️ 

Would love to hear your thoughts on the video below ❤️

Thank you for the good times @auroraarktika 

#Iceland​ #sailtoski​ #Westfjords

node.text:
2021 ✨ It certainly didn’t go as I thought it would, but still this year has been one very special year with many great adventures, good friends and lots of important life lessons. 

Here’s a little summary of my highlights from the past year. 

I started the year recovering from a knee surgery, which took its toll on me. I realised it would be a winter without skiing and hiking. But I was determined to make the most out of it anyway. I travelled all over Iceland on crutches, with great help from friends and Leo. That would drag me around over a frozen glacier lagoon on a sled. 😆 Just so that I didn’t have to miss out on epic adventures and projects. 

Then in the spring, Iceland started shaking. With multiple earthquakes. Seeing a live erupting volcano from only meters away is something I never thought I’d experience and will live in my memories forever. 🌋 

In the famous volcano month, I found out that I was pregnant. At the same time as @catkoppel moved in with us for a month and brought our Van over to Iceland all the way from Sweden. What a legend! 😄

Then me and Leo moved into our van for almost half a year and went full explore mode. 

We hosted 3x sold out events with @vanlife_iceland and sneaked in a both a sailing trip in Croatia and a road-trip to the Alps. 

The last picture is a simple reminder to appreciate what we have and stay positive. This image was taken at one of my first hikes after my knee surgery and I was so happy to be able to hike all the way up without pain in my knee!

Happy new year to you all, see you in 2022 ❤️ 
Then we will be three 3️⃣

node.text:
Proof that Social Media is fake 😆

Ok this is an extreme scenario. I’m used to the calmness of the Icelandic nature and always being far away from crowds.

In Japan it was a completely different story and it felt like every photogenic spot was crowded with people each time. 

This is The Hakone Shrine. At least the Japanese people are so polite that everyone just lines up and wait for their turn ☺️😆

Oh well, I just think it’s fun to show you guys this side of social media as well. 

#SocialMedia #Japan

node.text:
Iceland is shaking, again 🌋 
We woke up at 5am to the house and bed shaking. With this little daylight it felt apocalyptic 😆

Apparently the lava sits on a 2km-5km depth. Trying to break its way through the surface. But it can go either way, cool down or go full eruption again. 

But this is our new norm here in the capital area. The beast has woken and Reykjanes Peninsula has gone into an active phase that can last for hundred years.

Will you visit Iceland to witness an eruption with your own eyes? ☺️

#IcelandVolcano #Volcano

node.text:
Life at sea. Sailing for sustainability.
One of the most memorable trip this year is sailing from North of Iceland to the South. I was around 8 weeks pregnant and it’s one of the hardest expeditions I’ve ever been on. I usually never get seasick, but in this trip due to the pregnancy I was vomiting non-stop, completely out of energy and simply trying to survive. 

But I’m glad I pushed through. The scenery, the people and the adventure will live in my memories forever. But those first three months of pregnancy are HARD!! Jeez, I’m glad that is over. 

Also I had a lot of mental support from @catkoppel that shared cabin with me. Poor her while I was vomiting in a tiny bowl in our room on the rocky boat 😆

Thank you for another adventure @oceanmissionsiceland , @northsailing , @66north ⛵️

node.text:
The day I had Skógafoss waterfall to myself.  The world was in lockdown and Icelandic nature was so empty. 

This experiences was surreal, it reminded me of being 16years old. Exploring Iceland with my parents. Before tourism started in Iceland. Then it was totally normal to be alone in these places. 

But today I realise that these moments will probably never come again and that’s ok. 

But I’ll never forget what it’s like to sit in front of this waterfall completely alone with the loud noises of the falling water. 

#Iceland
